### GET /api/users

This endpoint retrieves a list of users.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

#### Response

The response will be a JSON array containing user objects with the following properties:

- `id_users` (number): The unique identifier for the user.

- `name` (string): The name of the user.

- `email` (string): The email address of the user.

- `password` (string): The password of the user.


Example response:

``` json
[
    {
        "id_users": 0,
        "name": "",
        "email": "",
        "password": ""
    }
]

 ```

#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "array",
    "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
            "id_users": {
                "type": "number"
            },
            "name": {
                "type": "string"
            },
            "email": {
                "type": "string"
            },
            "password": {
                "type": "string"
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

The `POST /api/section/` endpoint is used to create a new section. The request should include the `id_users` and `title` parameters in the request body.

### Request Body
- `id_users` (number, required): The ID of the user to whom the section belongs.
- `title` (string, required): The title of the section.

### Response (JSON Schema)
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "id_users": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "title": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

The `POST /api/task` endpoint is used to create a new task. The request should include a JSON payload with the `title`, `body`, and `id_section` fields.

### Request Body

- `title` (string, required): The title of the task.

- `body` (string, required): The body/content of the task.

- `id_section` (number, required): The ID of the section to which the task belongs.


### Response

The response of this request is a JSON schema representing the structure of the response object. It should include the properties and their data types that the API will return upon successful creation of a task.

For example:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "title": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "body": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "id_section": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "createdAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "updatedAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    }
  }
}

 ```

## Update Task

This endpoint is used to update a specific task identified by its ID.

### Request

- Method: PUT

- URL: `localhost:3005/api/task/14`

- Body:
    - title (string, optional): The title of the task.

    - body (string, optional): The content/body of the task.

    - id_section (number, optional): The ID of the section to which the task belongs.


### Response

The response for this request is a JSON object conforming to the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```
